The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques to optimize the motion of a human musculoskeletal model, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, to achieve this optimization, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of physics-based simulation environments, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY).
